com.conceptwave.scripting
Class CwObject

com.conceptwave.scripting.Object
  com.conceptwave.scripting.CWScriptable
      com.conceptwave.scripting.CwObject
Direct Known Subclasses:
Controller, CwAbstractTest, DataStructure, DecisionTree, Finder, OrderItem, Process, ReferenceTable, WorklistItem
public class CwObject
extends CWScriptable

Base type of all data objects. This is an abstract type that does not have constructor - i.e. a script cannot create objects of the derived types only.

parent

public CwObject parent
READWRITE: Parent data object. For hierarchical objects such as DataStructures and Orders, upper-level nodes will be returned as the parent for child nodes. If created explicitly in script, the parent property of top nodes will be NULL. If the result of an Finder, the finder will be parent of top nodes. For DataStructures, if a top-level DataStructure is assigned to a child node of another DataStructure(automatically or explicitly in script) its parent will be not be NULL and will be the containing object. NOTE: Prior to 5.1.14, the parent property of DataStructure child nodes was always NULL. This could be used to detect if a node object was an instance of a DataStructure node (as opposed to a child node in an order object where the parent property would return a NON-NULL object.). In 5.1.14 and later, the parent property can no longer be used to distinguish between DataStructure child nodes and Order child nodes. However, the JavaScript "instanceof" operator can be used to detect the type of child node or parent node. Sets parent data object

deleteFromDB

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer deleteFromDB(String destination,
                                                      DatabaseConnection c)
Delete a record from the database for the current data structure.

Script Example: 

 var customerDs = new mynamespace.customer();
 customerDs.id = "10013";
 var count = customerDs.deleteFromDB("ORDER", true);

Parameters:
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
con - Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - Implicit parameter for user context
Returns:
deleted record count as integer for supported database, in Cassandra it will always return zero.

deleteFromDBById

public static com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer deleteFromDBById(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] id,
                                                                 String name,
                                                                 String destination,
                                                                 DatabaseConnection con)
Delete a record from the database for the current data structure. It accepts an array of the key column value as id parameter and schema mapping as destination parameter. Here array of ids does not mean it accept multiple values for same key column, but when there are multiple key columns associated with single DBMap then array of IDs will accept value for each key columns. The CwfScriptDBConnection parameter is optional, if it is passed then it will use that connection, otherwise it use the connection associated with given destination schema. On success, it return delete count. Some databases, i.e. Cassandra, does not support delete count, so it will return zero always. In such cases, reading back the record required to confirm successful deletion.

Script Example:Order DBMaps has two key columns, OrderID and CustomerID 

 var deletedCount = CwObject.deleteFromDBById(["ORD_10016","CUST_10020"], "mynamespace.customer", 'ORDER');

Parameters:
id - A key column values as object array.
name - Qualified name ( namespace.datastructure) of the data structure
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
con - Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - Implicit parameter for user context
Returns:
deleted record count as integer for supported database, in Cassandra it will always return zero.

formattedValue

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Object formattedValue(String path)
In pre-Velocity mode, returns formatted visual representation of a given document leaf as string. In Velocity mode, returns the formatted string only if the leaf is a reference, enumeration, or a translation. Otherwise the leaf value is returned. Throws exception if the leaf does not exist. If the leaf has null value returns empty string.

Parameters:
path - Leaf name.
Returns:
Formatted value of the specified leaf as string.

insertInDB

public void insertInDB(String destination,
                       DatabaseConnection con)
Insert data in to the database for the current data structure. It accepts schema mapping as destination parameter. The CwfScriptDBConnection parameter is optional, if it is passed then it will use that connection, otherwise it use the connection associated with given destination schema

Script Example: 

 var customerDs = new mynamespace.customer();
 customerDs.name = "myname";
 ...
 ...
 customerDs.email = "me@mysite.com";
 customerDs.insertInDB("ORDER");

Parameters:
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
cascade - if true, then given data structure with also rerive associated child data structure from the database.
con - Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - Implicit parameter for user context
See Also:
#saveToDB(String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #updateInDB(String, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext)

mapTo

public Array mapTo(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object target,
                   String mapName,
                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean throwException,
                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean changedOnly,
                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean runTriggers,
                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean ignoreNull)
Maps the current object to the data object specified as parameter using the specified mapping. If the no conversion map is found that satisfies the requirements, no mapping is done.

Parameters:
target - The target data object or or fully specified target data object metadata name.
mapName - The conversion map name or tag. If null the default conversion map will be used.
throwException - If true throws exceptions if the conversion map/default conversion map does not exist.
changedOnly - if true only values that are different than their persisted (database) values are copied. Ignored if data object does not support persistence (i.e. data structure).
runTriggers - If true trigger flags are set on changed target fields. Trigger scripts for those fields will be executed when requested by the UI or by metadata (CwObject.runTriggers()). If false, flags will cleared on the target.
ignoreNull - If true target nodes will NOT be overwritten with NULL values from the source. If false target nodes may be set to NULL if the source node is NULL.
Returns:
Array of target objects

readFromDB

public CwObject readFromDB(String destination,
                           com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean cascade,
                           DatabaseConnection con)
Retrive data from the database for the current data structure. It can also read child data structure record if cascade parameter set to true. The CwfScriptDBConnection parameter is optional, if it is passed then it will use that connection, otherwise it will use the connection associated with given destination schema.

Script Example: 

 var customerDs = new mynamespace.customer();
 customerDs.id = "10016";
 customerDs.readFromDB("ORDER");

Parameters:
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping, if it is not supplied then it will use default database schema mapping.
cascade - if true, then given data structure with also rerive associated child data structure from the database.
con - Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - Implicit parameter for user context
Returns:
CwfDataObject (CwObject) that contains values from database as per data structure properties.
See Also:
#readFromDBById(Object[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #readFromDBByReference(Object[], String[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #selectFromDB(String, Object[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext)

readFromDBById

public static CwObject readFromDBById(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] id,
                                      String name,
                                      String destination,
                                      com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean cascade,
                                      DatabaseConnection con)
Retrive data from the database for given data structure. It accept array of key column value as id parameter and schema mapping as destination parameter. Here array of ids does not mean it accept multiple values for same key column, but when there are multiple key columns associated with single DBMap then array of IDs will accept value for each key columns. It can also retrive data for child data structure if cascade parameter set to true. The CwfScriptDBConnection parameter is optional, if it is passed then it will use that connection, otherwise it use the connection associated with given destination schema.

Script Example: Order DBMaps has two key columns, OrderID and CustomerID 

 var orderDs = CwObject.readFromDBById(["ORD_10016","CUST_10020"], "mynamespace.order", 'ORDER');

Parameters:
id - An array of key column values.
name - Qualified name (namespace.datastructure) of the data structure
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
cascade - (optional) if true, then given data structure with also rerive associated child data structure from the database.
con - (optional) Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - (implicit) User context
Returns:
CwfDataObject (CwObject) that contains values from database as per data structure properties.
See Also:
#readFromDB(String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #readFromDBByReference(Object[], String[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #selectFromDB(String, Object[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext)

readFromDBByReference

public static DataObjectList readFromDBByReference(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] val,
                                                   String[] column,
                                                   String name,
                                                   String destination,
                                                   com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean cascade,
                                                   DatabaseConnection con)
Retrive data from the database for given data structure. It accept array of key column value as id parameter and schema mapping as destination parameter. It can also retrive data for child data structure if cascade parameter set to true. The CwfScriptDBConnection parameter is optional, if it is passed then it will use that connection, otherwise it use the connection associated with given destination schema. Note: Cassandra support select queries only for primary key column. For Cassandra this method will work only if primary key column is used to get the records.

Script Example: 

 var custListA = CwObject.readFromDBByReference(["xyz"], ["name"], "mynamespace.customer",'order'); //single column
 var custListB = CwObject.readFromDBByReference(["xyz", 21], ["name", "age"], "mynamespace.customer",'order'); //multiple column

Parameters:
val - An array of the values
column - An array of the column names
name - Qualified name (namespace.datastructure) of the data structure
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
cascade - (optional) if true, then given data structure with also rerive associated child data structure from the database.
con - (optional) Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - (implicit) User context
Returns:
CwfDataObjectList (DataObjectList) contains values retrived from database as per data structure properties.
See Also:
#readFromDB(String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #readFromDBById(Object[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #selectFromDB(String, Object[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext)

resetLeafFlags

saveToDB

public void saveToDB(String destination,
                     com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean cascade,
                     DatabaseConnection con)
Save data to the database for the current data structure. It use to add new records in database or update existing record to the database. Internally it will call insert or update method based on data status. If data is read first then it will call updateInDB on save. If data never read, that means it is a new data then it will call insertInDB .

Script Example: 

 var customerDs = new mynamespace.customer();
 customerDs.id = "10016";
 customerDs.readFromDB("ORDER");
 customerDs.name = "updatedname";
 // this will call updateInDB, as it read from db before save.
 customerDs.saveToDB("ORDER");

Parameters:
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
con - Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - Implicit parameter for user context
See Also:
#updateInDB(String, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #insertInDB(String, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext)

selectFromDB

public static DataObjectList selectFromDB(String sql,
                                          com.conceptwave.scripting.Object[] param,
                                          String name,
                                          String destination,
                                          com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean cascade,
                                          DatabaseConnection jscon)
Retrive data from the database for given data structure using SQL. It accept SQL with parameters, and value of the parameter passed as seperate param array. Schema mapping can be specifiy as destination parameter. It can also retrive data for child data structure if cascade parameter set to true. The CwfScriptDBConnection parameter is optional, if it is passed then it will use that connection, otherwise it use the connection associated with given destination schema.

Script Example:

To get all the columns, use {+*+} and do not specify TABLE name or WHERE keyword, WHERE clause can be used directly with column name prefixed by Tn ( T0,T1,T2... etc). Table alias should be prefixed if multiple tables are associated with the mapping.

SELECT * FROM CUSTOMER WHERE ID = 10016 can be written as given example. 
 var custList = CwObject.selectFromDB("SELECT {+*+} ID = ?",["10016"], "mynamespace.customer",'order');
 OR for multiple tables...
 var custList = CwObject.selectFromDB("SELECT {+*+} T0.ID = ?",["10016"], "mynamespace.customer",'order');
TODO: Need to support partial (does not contain all columns) table queries. Presently it support limited cases.
Partial table queries should...
  • ...maintain same order as DBMap for columns
  • ...must not skip any column.
E.g. If table has 10 columns (col01... col10), and queries only need 3 columns then SQL statement looks like
SELECT col01, col06, col03 FROM XYZ WHERE colum1 = 10016 and it can be written as given example. Note: Cassandra support select queries only for primary key column. For Cassandra this method will work only if primary key column is used to get the records. 
 var custList = CwObject.selectFromDB("SELECT col01, col02, col03, col04, col05, col06 FROM XYZ WHERE col01 = ?",["10016"], "mynamespace.customer",'order');

Parameters:
sql - SQL statement, with certain limitation and specification, check examples.
param - An array of the parameters for SQL, pass blank array if no parameter used.
name - Qualified name (namespace.datastructure) of the data structure
destination - name of the database schema that used for database mapping
cascade - (optional) if true, then given data structure with also rerive associated child data structure from the database.
con - (optional) Optional parameter for database connection as CwfScriptDBConnection
cx - (implicit) User context
Returns:
CwfDataObjectList (DataObjectList) contains values retrived from database as per data structure properties.
See Also:
#readFromDB(String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #readFromDBById(Object[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext), #readFromDBByReference(Object[], String[], String, String, boolean, CwfScriptDBConnection, CwfContext)

public com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean setNoDBOperations(com.conceptwave.scripting.Object flag)
Sets or resets "Don't perform DB Operations" flag on the object. Make sense if the object is document or top level order. DB operations are ignored if the "Don't perform DB Operations" flag is set for the corresponding document or the top level order of the document.

Parameters:
flag - Object - if not boolean value no actions are done. Can be used to check the current value of the "Don't perform DB Operations" flag. If boolean value the "Don't perform DB Operations" flag is set (if the value is true) or reset otherwise.
Returns:
boolean - the value of the "Don't perform DB Operations" flag before it has been set or reset.

setRuleSetTag

public void setRuleSetTag(String tag)
Set a Rule Set tag to use for this object during validation and permission checks. If set the default Rule Set for this object might not be used (if it has none or a different tag). Passing null will the remove current tag and allow the default Rule Set (if defined) to be used. Passing a tag that is not defined will disable Rule Set processing on this object. Using this method has no affect on the tags set on existing child objects. However, any new children automatically created or set into this object will will be assigned the current tag of this object. For automatically created children, the current tag of this object may be used for initialization if initialization Rule Sets are run for the child.

Parameters:
tag - RuleSet tag to assign to this object.

toJson

public String toJson(com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean excludeHeader)
Converts the data object (document or datastructure) to Json String, This method could be overridden by its cwToJson script function. Notes: (1). Date or DateTime in its json date format (which is specified in its 'json format', ie, yyyy/MM/dd); if no date json format specified, default is GMT/UTC time in ISO-8601 standard: yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss.SSSZ for DateTime, yyyy-MM-dd for Date. the json format could also be '/Date', which should be '/Date(milliseconds)' format. (2). Escape: \ -> \\ " -> \" \r -> \\r \n -> \\n \b -> \\b \t -> \\t \f -> \\f

Parameters:

Returns:
The Json string.

validate

public Array validate(com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer maxNumOfErrors,
                      com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean returnCodes,
                      com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean validateCodes)
Validates the data object and returns a list of validation error messages in the user language. This function is for data objects like document orders or data structures, for all other types of data objects the method will return null.

Parameters:
maxNumOfErrors - Maximum number of errors.
returnCodes - If true, the result array will contain pairs of elements - error code and error message for each error.
validateCodes - Optional. If true the system will check if the code table values in the data documents are existing in the corresonding code table.
Returns:
A string array of error messages or null if no errors are found. Warnings and information messages are not returned. The messages are in the language defined by the current user context.
NOTE: If the first parameter 'maxNumOfErrors' is not specified or equals 0, the validation will stop when the first error is found.
In this case it will not return any error messages, but will change the status of the object so this.hasErrorStatus property will return true.

validateEx

public ValidationErrorList validateEx(com.conceptwave.scripting.Integer maxNumOfErrors,
                                      com.conceptwave.scripting.Boolean validateCodes)
Validates the data object and returns ValidationErrorList. This function is for data objects like document orders or data structures, for all other types of data objects the method will return null.

Parameters:
maxNumOfErrors - Maximum number of errors.
validateCodes - Optional. If true the system will check if the code table values in the data documents are existing in the corresonding code table.
Returns:
ValidationErrorList that contains validation errors or null if the object is valid.
NOTE: If the first parameter 'maxNumOfErrors' is not specified or equals 0, the validation will stop when the first error is found.
In this case the validation error list will be empty, but it will change the status of the object so this.hasErrorStatus property will return true.
